Integration test suite for `steno::parse_source`, ported from `test/parse.test.ts`. Exercises the fenced-entry/directive source format end-to-end, both against inline literal strings and the real `dict.steno` corpus read from the repo root (via `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR/../../dict.steno`).

Key coupling: `corpus()` reads the actual `dict.steno` file, so several tests (`corpus_parses`, `corpus_has_expected_directives`, `corpus_has_expected_struct_blocks`, `corpus_has_no_duplicate_strokes`, `corpus_is_non_trivial`) are load-bearing against that file's real content — editing `dict.steno` (adding/removing/renaming strokes, changing counts/arities/flags) will break these tests, and they must be updated together. Specific asserted facts about the corpus: >70 entries, no duplicate `stroke_raw` values, exactly 11 entries whose stroke starts with `STKWR-RBGT/` (data-structure selectors), specific count/arity/flag values for named strokes (e.g. `STKWR-PB` count `AOE`, `STKWR-PBGS/-FLT` count `None` since functions are "no-param now", `PR` arity `1`, `SKWR` arity `1` for Generator), and total template chunk count >50.

`SRC` is a shared three-entry fixture string (function/generic/switch strokes) used by `parses_entries_and_attaches_directives` to check stroke splitting on `/`, directive attachment (`@count`, `@arity`, `@multiline`) to the preceding entry, and that unspecified directives default to `None`/false.

`rejects_bad_source` enumerates specific invalid inputs (directive before any entry, unterminated block, stray closing fence, unexpected text, unknown directive, non-integer `@arity`) and asserts the error message contains a specific substring for each — if `parse_source`'s error messages change wording, update the `needle` strings here. `steno_error_carries_line_number` checks `StenoError::line()` returns 1-based line numbers.

Local helpers `by_stroke` (builds a `HashMap<&str, &Entry>` keyed by `stroke_raw`) and `entry` (lookup wrapper) are test-only conveniences, not part of the public API.